entry.title: Introduce LiveTicks on Windows
entry.content:
First described in bit.ly/chrome-clocks-and-sleep, `LiveTicks` is a

facility similar to `TimeTicks` that doesn't advance while the system

is suspended. There is more context about the larger, overarching work

in https://docs.google.com/document/d/1jUmRI_XDGj_vNU78zXE-z1Nv1UgOvtg6ovlSL-e66Ic/edit?usp=sharing



The implementation of `TimeTicks` on most platforms already conforms to

this contract, with the notable exception of Windows. This has

implications for task scheduling, among other things.



This CL introduces `LiveTicks` and adds support for it in

`ScopedTimeClockOverrides`. This is the first step towards defining

both `LiveTicks` and `BootTicks` on all platforms, and lets existing

code that needs `LiveTicks` explicitly use it. The first such piece of

code is in the dependent CL: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4480250



Bug: 1394810

entry.title: Fix offsets in FormatString() for RTL strings on Linux and ChromeOS
entry.content:
On Linux and ChromeOS, an extra base::i18n::kRightToLeftMark character

is appended for the text rendering engine to render the string

correctly.



This is done inside AdjustParagraphDirectionality().



Before this CL:

ReplaceStringPlaceholders() which computes the offsets was called

before AdjustParagraphDirectionality() which may append extra

characters. Therefore, the computed offsets could have been wrong.



After this CL:

AdjustParagraphDirectionality() is called before computing the offsets

in ReplaceStringPlaceholders() to make sure the compute offsets are

up-to-date.

entry.title: Use ANGLE extension to skip texture renderability checks.
entry.content:
1. When a texture is created on GLES3 context and used/imported on GLES2

context, it could fail renderability validiation checks in ANGLE. This

is because texture could be created with a format in GLES3 context

which is invalid in GLES2 context.



Use ANGLE extension to set texture parameters using glTexParameteri to

skip ANGLE validation checks on that texture when it is used in GLES2

context.



This is used when we create texture in chrome in GLES3 context using

glTexStorage* which would result in using a sized format RGBA8 which is

not supported in GLES2 context resulting in ANGLE validation failures.



2. Enable gles3 with passthrough command decoder on Android.



3. Don't enable gles3 with passthrough on emulators for now.

We cannot generate good compile hints when some scripts are coming

hints, this is (hopefully) feasible.



In addition, try to figure out more accurately when we're going to

produce compile hints, and disable code cache only then.
